               <msContents>
                  <summary>Personal letter from Tourbon to his brother Dioskoros, asking him to send something, probably a cloak, and to raise a certain pig; lengthy salutation at the end</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; on the back the address along the fibers; the hand is large but becomes much smaller and faster as the writer picks up speed toward the bottom of the text</note>
                     <note type="general">The letter was probably written personally by Tourbon, like P.Col. X 279</note>
                     <note type="general">20 lines of writing; it is unclear how many lines, if any, are missing in the central part</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
